    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a museum-quality 2004 Honda S2000 (AP2), a definitive example of naturally aspirated precision. This chassis features the rigid X-bone frame architecture with zero signs of oxidation or stress. The F22C1 power plant exhibits optimal compression and a pristine valvetrain, delivering a sharp VTEC engagement at 6,000 RPM. Power is delivered through a close-ratio six-speed manual transmission to a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring exceptional corner-exit traction. The double-wishbone suspension remains tight with factory-spec bushings, and the vehicle retains its original VIN-matched body panels and paint. This is an unmolested, collector-grade specimen for the enthusiast who demands mechanical perfection and analog feedback.",
